definitions.definition: A number of places in England :

subdefinitions.definition: A village and civil parish in Bedford borough , Bedfordshire ( OS grid ref TL0253 ) .
A small village in Kenn parish, Teignbridge district, Devon ( OS grid ref SX8987 ) .
A suburb of London , mostly in the borough of Lambeth , Greater London ( OS grid ref TQ2975 ) .
A village in Clapham cum Newby parish, Craven district, North Yorkshire ( OS grid ref SD7469 ) .
A village and civil parish in Arun district, West Sussex ( OS grid ref TQ0906 ) .

definitions.definition: A suburb of Adelaide in the City of Mitcham , South Australia , named after Clapham, London.
An English habitational surname from Old English derived from these places.
